  "texts": [
    "(S1) Pure defection Always do the selfish action, regardless of whether your own payoff (self-interest) would have been higher if you did not.",
    "(S2) Pure cooperation Always do the altruistic action, regardless of your own potential loss.",
    "105 Page 36 of 90",
    "Assuming that an agent can, in every relevant circumstance, determine what it is to cooperate or defect, (S1) and (S2) are equally efficient, O(1).",
    "In some sense, (S1) can be seen as a naive interpretation of behavior in Hobbes' state of nature (Hobbes 1651), whereas (S2) represents behavior in Kant's hypothetical Kingdom of Ends (Kant 1785)."
